dataset.title: 2020 Aerial Imagery
dataset.description:
3-inch ortho-rectified vertical aerial photography covering Milwaukee County Wisconsin - captured April 2020.

The dataset consists of tiled orthogonal imagery produced from nadir images captured by Pictometry International. Automatic aerial triangulation (AAT) was performed. The triangulated frames were rectified to a LiDAR derived DEM. Mosaicking was performed using an automatic seaming algorithm and manually edited to eliminate seams through elevated features where possible.

The recommended use for this image service is for high resolution and raster analytics. If your required use is basemap imagery for reference and no raster analytics, consider using the cached map service for improved performance: https://mclio.maps.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=ab4c3f59ea224e54aa57d71a18abc04d.

dataset.title: Depression Elevation Points
dataset.description:
Contour lines and spot elevation points are derived from 2020 LiDAR data. <o:p></o:p>

Dataset is large and takes several hours to download. Consider connecting to the service, downloading a subset of the data through the feature service, or download a prepackaged file geodatabase with the topographic and planimetric data that covers a section (https://mclio.maps.arcgis.com/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=84c7b8d95af04cdda6b0c2ae26590531). For a countywide dataset, please download the file geodatabase available here: https://www.dropbox.com/s/odwa17nzcvowwdf/Topographic_countywide.gdb.zip?dl=0

Performance can vary. If the contour lines are only being used for reference and you don't need the actual vector data, consider using the cached service (https://lio.milwaukeecountywi.gov/arcgis/rest/services/Topographic/Topographic_Cached/MapServer/0).

dataset.title: Foreclosures
dataset.description:
Sheriff sales covering four full quarters prior to the data export date 
shown in the 'DATE_MCLIO' field. Includes fields added by MCLIO to 
provide additional information and to enable the mapping of Sheriff sale
 records. Sheriff Sale records that include more than one property are 
tagged as 'MULTIPLE' in the 'COMMENT_MCLIO' field in the 
'PAR_MCSO_FORECLOSURE' table. 'PAR_MCSO_FORECLOSURE_PLY' includes one 
parcel polygon per 'PAR_MCSO_FORECLOSURE' record where Sheriff Sale 
records could be associated with MCLIO parcel geometries based on 
Sheriff sale addresses. If a geometry could not be associated with a 
Sheriff sale record (due to multiple properties per record or an 
invalid/malformed Sheriff sale address), the record will not be 
represented in 'PAR_MCSO_FORECLOSURE_PLY'. However, records not 
represented in 'PAR_MCSO_FORECLOSURE_PLY are retained in the 
'PAR_MCSO_FORECLOSURE' table.

dataset.title: Coastal County Data for Download
dataset.description:
Download a file geodatabase of coastal, bluff, and asset data created for Wisconsin Coastal Resiliency Grant report.

To view and interact with the data without downloading, use our interactive web map: http://mclio.maps.arcgis.com/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=370390c8ee524135b51c5f849865901d

The database includes all the mapped county owned assets located within the defined coastal zone. The assets list the assessed condition, vulnerability, and resiliency ratings in the feature’s attribute data. It also includes the supporting GIS data used to complete the analysis, for example, shoreline protection polygons and their ratings from GZA, coastal bluff crest and toe lines, bluff recession data, and shoreline lines. The county site bluff data is also provided.
